  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently caught in active hedging mode with SPX at 6521 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6475 (-4B) and positive gamma at 6525 (+1.8B) - they're likely buying the breakout above the flip line but will aggressively sell any push toward 6525 resistance. The breakout regime with -2.5B total GEX means dealers will amplify moves in both directions, creating a volatile rangebound environment between 6475-6525 until one of these major gamma walls breaks decisively. Watch 6525 closely - a break above triggers dealer selling into strength, while any retreat toward 6475 will see heavy dealer buying that could spark another leg higher.",
